parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the subframe can cause the vehicle to become disabled, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual noises
vibrations
or pulling to one side while driving. The front tires may be out of position
and the vehicle may be difficult to steer. In severe cases
the subframe may collapse
causing the vehicle to become immobile.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of the subframe can cause the vehicle's suspension and steering components to separate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's front end alignment is off
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering feels loose or unstable
the front tires are unevenly worn
the vehicle makes a clunking or squeaking noise
the front wheel(s) become misaligned or separated from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Recall Coverage for 1999 Hyundai Sonata
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of recall coverage for the 1999 Hyundai Sonata models may leave owners unaware of the potential safety risks associated with subframe corrosion and failure, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Owners of 1999 Hyundai Sonata models may not be notified of the recall or may be denied coverage despite experiencing similar issues
leaving them to bear the cost of repairs or replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and failure of the engine cradle can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to potential accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: The engine cradle is rusted
the arm comes out of the cradle
the vehicle is declared unsafe to drive
the alignment is off
and the vehicle may have a hole in the engine cradle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine racing and stalling can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, leading to potential accidents or loss of power.
symptoms: The engine RPMs increase without notice
the engine RPMs fluctuate between high and low
the engine almost cuts off when accelerating
the vehicle smells gas
and the engine may flood.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Oxygen Sensor and Exhaust System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty oxygen sensor and exhaust system can cause the vehicle to emit black smoke, have difficulty starting, and trigger the check engine light.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle emits black smoke
the vehicle has difficulty starting
and the exhaust system may have a leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Fluid Issues and Spark Plug Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission fluid issues and spark plug failure can cause the vehicle to have difficulty shifting, stall, or have difficulty starting.
symptoms: The transmission fluid is low
the spark plug wires are fried
the vehicle has difficulty shifting
and the vehicle may stall or have difficulty starting.
